28/09/2006
TIRANA, Albania -- Attending a meeting of regional defence ministers in Tirana on Wednesday (27 September), Bulgaria's Vesselin Bliznakov announced that his country has agreed to deploy a frigate for a two-month mission with the UN Force in Lebanon, starting in mid-October. 
The "Drazki", with a crew of 130, would conduct patrols in Lebanon's waters, pending approval by the Bulgarian parliament. 
(Sega - 28/09/06; BNR, Darik - 27/09/06)
